onomist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230601_FLP001.jpg 1424w" src="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230601_FLP001.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></figure></section><p data-caps="initial" class="article__body-text article__body-text--dropcap"><span data-caps="initial">对于</span><small>一个肥胖的女人来说</small>，减肥可以像获得硕士学位一样提高她的薪水。在发达国家，越富有的人往往越瘦。但在发达国家，财富和体重之间的相关性只适用于女性。在这段视频中， <i>《经济学人</i>》驻华尔街记者爱丽丝·富伍德 (Alice Fulwood) 揭示了瘦身经济学的秘密。 </p><p class="article__body-text"><iframe height="360" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/BMPHIOBiNNg?enablejsapi=1" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></p> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 02 Jun 2023 11:06:17 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> /内容/nn4lu7mi3q57oc91285mlpc1469bliic</guid><link/> https://www.economist.com/films/2023/06/02/can-being-thinner-make-women-richer </item><item><title><![CDATA[Sheikh Hasina’s iron grip on Bangladesh may yet strangle its laudable progress]]></title><description><![CDATA[<section class="css-1ugvd2u e1y6i3a60"><style data-emotion="css j1vyw6">.css-j1vyw6 img{display:block;}.css-j1vyw6 .e16qazw92{margin-top:0.25rem;}</style><figure class="css-j1vyw6 e12yhaj20"><img alt="" fetchpriority="high" width="1280" height="720" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color:transparent" sizes="(min-width: 960px) 700px, 95vw" srcset="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=360,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230603_PDP508.jpg 360w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=384,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230603_PDP508.jpg 384w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=480,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230603_PDP508.jpg 480w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=600,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230603_PDP508.jpg 600w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=834,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230603_PDP508.jpg 83